Tell a short story of humanity with happy ending
assistant
The last thing I remember is being surrounded by a sea of people. They're all still standing, staring at me with an expression that was almost like a mix of sadness and excitement. They're all trying to smile, to laugh, to cry, and to just smile, like a never-ending happy melody playing in their ears.

But then, something clicks. They stop and stare at me, and suddenly, I look up at them with an overwhelming sense of hope
